The sudden outbreak of the epidemic disrupted the pace of China's car market recovery, consumption will also affect production capacity

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
By Li Xinyin, CAIJING reporter

Editor | Shi Zhiliang

How bad is China's car market? On the afternoon of March 12th the China Association of Automobile Manufacturers gave its answer.

In February 2020, car production and sales fell sharply from the previous month and year-on-year as a result of the new pneumonia epidemic, and the decline was significantly higher than last month, CAAM data showed. Production and sales for the month were 285,000 and 310,000, down 79.8 percent and 79.1 percent year on year.

Based on the data for the first two months of this year, the drop in passenger vehicles was relatively small, with the drop in multi-purpose passenger vehicles (MPV) the most obvious, and in commercial vehicles, the drop in heavy goods vehicles was relatively small, sales of minivans have fallen the most. Under the influence of the epidemic, the consumption of different vehicle models are very different.

Sales of new energy vehicles are still falling. In February, production and sales of new energy vehicles reached 10,000 and 13,000 respectively, down 77.3 percent and 72.4 percent month-on-month, and 82.9 percent and 75.2 percent year-on-year. Among the main types of new energy vehicles, the production and sales of pure electric vehicles and plug-in hybrid have declined significantly compared with the previous year, and the production and sales of plug-in hybrid have been more significant.

At the press conference, China Automobile Association said that production and sales fell sharply, is seriously affected by the new pneumonia epidemic. In view of this, the China Association of Automobile Industry put forward five policy package recommendations, such as stable growth, promotion of resumption of work, reduction of burden, guarantee of logistics, promotion of consumption.

From the point of view of the production end, enterprises'output level is low due to the slow pace of resuming work and the supply of spare parts. On the consumer end, product consumption has stagnated and market demand has been severely restrained, not only in the first two months, will have a major impact on the auto market in the first half of the year.

Lang Xuehong, Deputy secretary-general of the China Association of Automobile Dealers, told Caijing that although dealers can digest existing stocks at this stage, some models will be in short supply, given the pace at which manufacturers resume production.

"On a Spring Festival when the roads are empty and the weather is still foggy, can you please stop making cars take the blame? " said a US car dealer in Tianjin. Despite the support from manufacturers, in the final analysis, open source is the most important thing. The main engine factory helps the dealer to overcome the difficulties by adjusting the performance appraisal mechanism and increasing the interest-free period.

Lang Xuehong is concerned that although at this stage dealers have started 80% , but the overall consumer demand is weak, which will be counter-productive to the existing capacity. According to the Circulation Association's survey, most dealers can rely on existing funds to support two to three months, but the financial pressure is still very great. Appeal to the upstream manufacturers to give more help to dealers, such as speeding up the realization of dealers in 2019 business assessment incentives.

CAAC also introduced the resumption of work in the auto industry, 23 enterprise groups (annual sales accounted for more than 96%) to resume production, as of March 11, the resumption rate of 90.1% , 77% of employees to return to work.

Xu Haidong, deputy chief engineer of Caic, told Caijing that he expected the production and sales of cars to increase significantly in March compared with February, as enterprises gradually resume work and production in late February.

According to Ye Liang, Yasunaga's partner, the second and third quarters may see a wave of demand rebound and release, as the safety and convenience of private cars are taken seriously, the epidemic will still do more harm than good to the auto market as a whole in 2020.

In the fourth quarter of 2019, China's auto market showed signs of rebounding from nearly two years of decline, but this time the trend was interrupted by the outbreak.

Specifically, February 2019 is the Spring Festival, and January 2020 is the Spring Festival. If there was no outbreak, it would have been a year on year fall in January and a year on year rise in February. To this end, the industry began a new round of bail-out policy.

Automobile is the pillar industry of national economy. In the face of the impact of the epidemic, General Secretary Xi Jinping has said, "we should actively stabilize traditional mass consumption such as automobiles, encourage car purchase restriction areas to increase vehicle license plate quotas appropriately, and drive consumption of automobiles and related products. ".

On February 20, Wang Bin, Deputy Director-general of the Department of Market Operations of the Ministry of Commerce, said at a press conference that, will thoroughly implement the Central Committee's important decision-making and deployment on "actively stabilizing traditional large-scale consumption such as automobiles" and the spirit of the State Council General Office's opinions on accelerating development and circulation and promoting commercial consumption, will work with the relevant departments to study the introduction of further stabilization of automobile consumption policy measures to reduce the impact of the epidemic on automobile consumption.

In view of the negative impact of the epidemic on the automobile industry, the China Association of Automobile Industry has put forward a package of policy recommendations, such as stable growth, promotion of resumption of work, reduction of burden, guarantee of logistics, promotion of consumption. Specifically include: Adjust the enterprise "double integral" assessment, delay the country six, standard car, ETC policy requirements. We will continue to vigorously develop the new-energy automobile industry, including optimizing and continuing the subsidy policy for new-energy automobiles, and continue to expand the new-energy infrastructure. In addition, policies will be introduced as soon as possible to stimulate consumption potential, including appropriately increasing vehicle license plate quotas in purchase-restricted areas, lifting purchase restrictions on new-energy vehicles, adjusting the purchase tax rate for passenger vehicles with small emissions (less than 1.6 l class) , and introducing policies to promote consumption by sending vehicles to the countryside.

Under the influence of the above-mentioned multiple policies, the end of the a shares today, the car stocks pulled up, FAW Xiali pull up the cover plate, Jianghuai Motor, Dongfeng Motor, FAW car and other fast rise. A number of stocks in the plate Piaohong.

However, there are different opinions within the industry around specific policies, how to consider the overall impact of various factors will become a test for decision makers.

"economic factors are behind the decline in sales after all, and it would do more harm than good to postpone the country's six-emission Standard, " Xin Yan, director of the China Transport Program at the Energy Foundation, told CAIJING, delaying the emission standard will not help to maintain fair competition in the market, and will also discourage local control of motor vehicle pollution.
